  "response_text": "A bright, airy living room appears, with white carpeting, floor-to-ceiling windows, and a wide green lawn and trees visible outside. A small fluffy white dog sits on the pale carpet near a round glass coffee table. The room is neat and modern: a light gray sofa with pillows and a throw blanket sits behind the table, a wooden cabinet stands to the left, and the coffee table holds a tall beige vase and a clear glass vessel.\n\nThe little dog turns and trots toward the sofa, then springs up onto it. It stands on the cushions, its white fur blending with the light upholstery. A young adult woman with long light-brown hair, fair skin, a pale gray short-sleeved top, blue jeans, and light shoes walks in from the right. She looks toward the dog with a gentle smile. A closer view of her face shows her smiling softly, eyes lowered as if watching the dog or the floor.\n\nShe kneels on the carpet beside the coffee table. A red trigger spray bottle stands upright next to her, and she uses a white cloth to scrub a spot on the carpet. The dog lies on the sofa behind her, watching over the edge of the cushion. The woman’s posture is bent forward and focused, one hand braced on the carpet while the other rubs with the cloth. The room remains spotless-looking and sunlit, with the pale carpet dominating the space.\n\nThe view pulls upward to reveal the living room arranged inside a large, shallow, circular dish, like a petri dish. Furniture, the woman, and the dog become small within the round white boundary. Pale gray circular marks and purple blotches begin to appear across the carpeted area, visually suggesting hidden contamination spreading around the clean-looking room.\n\nThe woman then walks across the living room toward a wooden cabinet. She opens a lower cabinet door. Inside, a blue Woolite spray bottle sits on a shelf in front of stacked wooden slats and folded cloths. The bottle has a gray trigger with a lime-green nozzle and label accents. Its front label reads “Woolite” and “sanitize,” with additional smaller pet-stain-and-odor wording. Small white legal text appears along the bottom of the screen, stating that Woolite is a trademark of Reckitt Benckiser licensed to BISSELL Homecare, Inc. The woman reaches in, grips the bottle by the neck, and lifts it out.\n\nBack by the sofa and carpet, she holds the Woolite bottle in one hand and leans down toward the floor. A close view shows her wiping the carpet again with a white cloth. A faint brownish stain is visible on the pale carpet. She brings the blue Woolite trigger bottle into view, aiming its nozzle toward the stain. Her wrist has a simple bracelet, and her hand holds the sprayer steadily above the spot. The product label is partly visible as she positions it over the stained area.\n\nThe imagery then shifts to an enlarged, stylized view of carpet fibers. Beige looped strands of carpet rise like soft columns, and small purple and green germ-like shapes cling among the fibers. Blue on-screen text appears across the center: “KILLS 99.9% OF BACTERIA.” The bacteria-like shapes remain scattered among the fibers while the bold text stays prominent.\n\nThe woman is then back in the living room, kneeling on the pale carpet and smiling broadly. The little white dog rushes into her arms, and she laughs visually, leaning forward with delight as she gathers it close. The blue Woolite spray bottle now stands upright on the carpet near her knee, with the white cloth nearby. She cuddles the dog against her chest, holding it securely while it faces outward, its dark eyes visible through its fluffy white fur. The sofa, coffee table, pillows, and sunny windows remain in the background, reinforcing the clean, bright home setting.\n\nThe product is then presented alone on the pale carpet in front of a softly blurred window. The blue Woolite Advanced Pet Stain and Odor Remover plus Sanitize bottle stands upright beside a crumpled white cleaning cloth. A dark badge near the top of the label reads “KILLS 99.9%.” Blue text appears to the right: “DON’T JUST CLEAN. SANITIZE.” A light blue curved graphic sweeps behind the text.\n\nFinally, the product lineup appears against a clean pale blue-white background. The central bottle is the same Woolite “sanitize” trigger spray. Additional Woolite cleaning products stand on either side, including tall aerosol-style cans with bright green caps. Large blue “Woolite” branding appears to the right, completing the product display.",
